SIMPLE: wearish
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wearish
<hw>Wear"ish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Etymol. uncertain,
but perhaps akin to <ets>weary</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Weak; withered; shrunk.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>wearish</xex> hand.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Ford.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A little, <qex>wearish</qex> old man, very melancholy by
nature.</q> <rj><qau>Burton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Insipid; tasteless; unsavory.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Wearish</qex> as meat is that is not well tasted.</q>
<rj><qau>Palsgrave.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wearisome</ent>⟦br⟧
